cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with embedding egocentric object interaction videos and analyzing their semantic labels using motion and appearance features. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach for estimating probability distribution over potential semantic labels using a semantic-visual graph. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing videos and their semantic labels. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new approach for interpreting and analyzing videos using semantic embeddings. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing and categorizing videos based on their semantic labels.
